File ptr : that points to this structure and is used to access the file 
where as : structuure -- is file the create for operning file



FILE*fptr : pointer

FILE*fptr;
fptr = fopen("filename",mode); // open
fclose(fptr); // close;


Reading from the file: 

char ch;
fscanf(fptr,"%c",&ch);


Writing to a file:

char ch = 'a';
fprintf(fptr,"%c",ch);


--> fgetc(fptr)  : read a char
--> fputc('A',fptr)   : write a char


EOF : fgetc return eof to show fiel has ended